===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French [[turbot#French|turbot]], from Old Swedish [[tornbut]], from [[törn]] ‘thorn’ + [[but]] ‘butt, flatfish’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈtɜ:bət/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''turbot'''|'''turbot''' or '''[[turbots]]'''}}

# Any of various [[flatfish]]es of family ''Scophthalmidae'' that are found in marine or brackish waters. 

